The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Tuesday, January 06, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Tuesday, January 6, 2004				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	A religious procession to celebrate 20 years of a Ganesh mandir will start at 11 am from Rabindra Sarani. It will proceed along Kalakar Street, Burtola, Mahatma Gandhi Road, Sonapatti and Prasanna Kumar Tagore Street, to return to Rabindra Sarani.				 																																	Southern Avenue. The Calcutta district Left Front will hold a nagarik convention at Nazrul Mancha at 5 pm.				 																Fairy tale				 																																	The Beastly Beatitudes film festival presents The Secret Adventures of Tom Thumb, Dave Borthicks post-modern sci-fi version of the old fairy tale, at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 6 pm.				 																Film fest				 																																	Pirosmani and Sergei Paradzhanovs Ashik Kerib to be screened as part of Fictional Truths  Beyond Festival, a session of alternative cinema presented by the Eisenstein Cine Club amp; Drik India, at Gorky Sadan, 6 pm.				 																Art watch				 																																	Small wonders, an exhibition of works by Paritosh Sen, Rabin Mondal, Prakash Karmakar and Sanat Kar, at Vikalp Art Shop, Swabhumi, from 2 pm to 8 pm.				 																																	An exhibition of paintings by Kalyani Roy, at Chitrakoot Art Gallery, from 3 pm to 8 pm.				 																																	The Homecoming  A Winter Symphony, an exhibition of Indian art and sculpture, featuring works of artists like Ramananda Bandopadhyay, Ganesh Haloi and Paritosh Sen, at Idiyas Gallery, from 10.30 am to 7.30 pm.				 																																	An exhibition of paintings by Dibyendu Basu, Nabendu Roy and Subrata Sankar Sen, at Prosceniums Art Centre, 4 pm.
